      • autofillAddress

        public static void autofillAddress(AddressFillable address,
                                   java.lang.String triggerField)
        Autofills the address if there is a unique match.
        Parameters:
        address - the address to autofill.
        triggerField - a list of comma separated address field names that are the values used to trigger the autofill.

      • autofillAddress

        public static void autofillAddress(AddressFillable address,
                                   java.lang.String triggerField,
                                   boolean alwaysOverride)
        Autofills the address if there is a unique match.
        Parameters:
        address - the address to autofill.
        triggerField - name of the address field that triggered the autofill.
        alwaysOverride - if true, override the existing value with the match for every address field (note, it could be null). If false, existing value for the field will not be overridden if the match is null.

      • getAutofillValue

        public static java.lang.Object getAutofillValue(Country country,
                                                java.lang.String fieldName,
                                                java.lang.String[] fieldNames,
                                                java.lang.Object[] fieldValues)
        This method wraps this.getAutofillValue() passing in false for the doOverride property.
        Parameters:
        country - the country
        fieldName - the field name to get the value for
        fieldNames - the field names you are supplying values for in the fieldValues array
        fieldValues - the field values corresponding with the fieldNames array
        Returns:
        Either a typekey or string with the value

      • getAutofillValue

        public static java.lang.Object getAutofillValue(Country country,
                                                java.lang.String fieldName,
                                                java.lang.String[] fieldNames,
                                                java.lang.Object[] fieldValues,
                                                boolean doOverride)
        Gets the value for the specified address field named fieldName based on address auto-fill configuration. The country parameter is used when it is not specified in the fieldNames and fieldValues
        Parameters:
        country - the country
        fieldName - the name of the field to autofill
        fieldNames - an array of the names of the fields on the address whose values will be used to determine the autofill value.
        fieldValues - an array of values of the fields on the address; there is a one-to-one correlation between the fieldNames and fieldValues
        doOverride - if true, override the existing value even if it is not null
        Returns:
        the value for the specified field, if there is a unique match or if there are multiple matches and one of the matches matches the current value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the length of fieldNames does not equal the length of fieldValues.

      • getAutofillValue

        public static java.lang.Object getAutofillValue(Country country,
                                                java.lang.String fieldName,
                                                java.lang.String[] fieldNames,
                                                java.lang.Object[] fieldValues,
                                                boolean doOverride,
                                                java.lang.Integer triggerIndex)
        Gets the value for the specified address field named fieldName based on address auto-fill configuration. Use this API if the country does not trigger reflection and is therefore not passed in the list of fields.
        Parameters:
        country - the country; this is ignored if the array of fields passed in contains the country
        fieldName - the name of the field to autofill
        fieldNames - an array of the names of the fields on the address whose values will be used to determine the autofill value.
        fieldValues - an array of values of the fields on the address; there is a one-to-one correlation between the fieldNames and fieldValues
        doOverride - if true, override the existing value even if it is not null
        triggerIndex - the index of the field that triggered the autofill.
        Returns:
        the value for the specified field, if there is a unique match or if there are multiple matches and one of the matches matches the current value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the length of fieldNames does not equal the length of fieldValues.

      • validate

        public static java.lang.String validate(AddressFillable address,
                                        java.lang.String addressFieldName)
        Validate the address field's format and value. This validates the field's format against a validator (if defined) and also validates that the field matches the other fields in the address (based on zone data). Returns an error message if there is an error with the address field, otherwise, returns null.
        Parameters:
        address - the address
        addressFieldName - the name of the address field
        Returns:
        an error message if there is an error with the address field, otherwise, returns null.

This validates the field's format against a validator (if defined) and also validates that the field matches the other fields in the address (based on zone data). Returns an error message if there is an error with the address field, otherwise, returns null.

      • getOrLookupZoneCode

        public static java.lang.String getOrLookupZoneCode(AddressFillable address,
                                                   ZoneType zoneType)
        Returns the zone code for the given address and zone type. If the value is not set in the address, it tries to lookup the value based on other values in the address. If there are multiple matches, it returns the first match, and the matches are ordered by the zone name.
        Parameters:
        address - the address
        zoneType - the zone type
        Returns:
        the zone code for the given address and zone type

      • getOrLookupZoneCode

        public static java.lang.String getOrLookupZoneCode(AddressFillable address,
                                                   ZoneType zoneType,
                                                   boolean uniqueOnly)
        Returns the zone code for the given address and zone type. If the value is not set in the address, it tries to lookup the value based on other values in the address.
        Parameters:
        address - the address
        zoneType - the zone type
        uniqueOnly - if true, only return the zone if it uniquely links to the zone being used in the lookup. If there is more than one match, then no zone is returned.
        Returns:
        the zone code for the given address and zone type, if none found, returns an empty string

      • lookupZone

        public static Zone lookupZone(AddressFillable address,
                              ZoneType zt,
                              boolean uniqueOnly)
        Look up the zone of the given zone type based on other zones in the address. The lookup is determined by the lookup order defined in zone config.
        Parameters:
        address - the address
        zt - the zone type that is being looked up
        uniqueOnly - if true, only return the zone if it uniquely links to the zone being used in the lookup. If there is more than one match, then no zone is returned.
        Returns:
        the zone if found, null otherwise.

      • getAddressFieldValue

        public static java.lang.Object getAddressFieldValue(Zone zone,
                                                    java.lang.String fieldName,
                                                    AddressFillable address)
        Return the zone value for the given zone and address field.
        Parameters:
        zone - the zone from which we will extract the zone name
        fieldName - the address field name
        address - the address
        Returns:
        the input zone value if the address field is not a typekey, if the address field is a typekey then it interprets the zone value as the type code and returns the corresponding type key

      • getValueRange

        public static java.lang.Object[] getValueRange(Country country,
                                               java.lang.String desiredFieldName,
                                               java.lang.String[] fieldNames,
                                               java.lang.Object[] fieldValues,
                                               java.lang.Integer triggerIndex)
        Get the value range for the desired field; the value range will be filtered by the other address fields that are passed in. For example, if the desired field is State, and the city is 'Paris' (with all other fields being null), the result would be all States that have a city called 'Paris'.
        Parameters:
        country - the country; note that this is ignored if country is in the array of fields
        desiredFieldName - the name of the field whose value range is being calculated.
        fieldNames - the names of the fields use to filter the value range
        fieldValues - the values of the fields that are used to filter the value range
        triggerIndex - the field that triggered this autofill call.
        Returns:
        the value range for the desired field
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the trigger index is out of range OR if the length of fieldNames does not equal the length of fieldValues

      • getValueRange

        public static <T> java.util.List<T> getValueRange(java.lang.String desiredFieldName,
                                                  java.lang.String triggerFieldName,
                                                  AddressFillable address,
                                                  java.lang.Object currentValue,
                                                  java.lang.Class<T> ofClass)
        Get the value range for the desired field; the value range will be filtered by the other address fields that are passed in. For example, if the desired field is State, and the city is 'Paris' (with all other fields being null), the result would be all States that have a city called 'Paris'.
        Parameters:
        desiredFieldName - the name of the field whose value range is being calculated.
        triggerFieldName - the field that is triggering the value range calculation.
        address - the address from whose fields the value range will be calculated
        currentValue - the current value of the desired field.
        ofClass - the class type of the value
        Returns:
        the value range for the desired field
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the trigger index is out of range OR if the length of fieldNames does not equal the length of fieldValues
